{
  "texts": [
    "For example, in iGeoTutor 12, Z3 (ref.",
    "33) is used to handle arithmetic inferences but algebraic manipulations are not covered.",
    "17) handles algebraic deductions by expressing them under a few limited deduction rules, therefore, it is unable to express more complex manipulations, leaving arithmetic inferences not covered.",
    "The most general treatment so far is a process similar that in ref.",
    "34 for angle-only theorem discovery and implemented in GeoLogic 19 for both angle and ratios."
  ]
